{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ἀσκέω</b>, <br /> <b>work</b> raw materials, εἴρια, κέρα, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 3.388, 4.110\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; <b>work curiously, form by art,</b> [κρητῆρα] Σιδόνες πολυδαίδαλοι εὖ ἤσκησαν[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. work] 23.743; ἑρμῖν᾽ ἀσκήσας 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 23.198\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; πτύξασα καὶ ἀσκήσασα χιτῶνα having folded and <b>smoothed</b> it,[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. work] 1.439; ἅρμα.. χρυσῷ καὶ ἀργύρῳ εὖ ἤσκηται 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 10.438\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; χορὸν ἤσκησεν[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. work] 18.592; γόμφοις ἀ. 5th c.BC: Empedocles Poeta Philosophus 87\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: added in <i>aorist</i> <i>participle</i> to Verbs, [θρόνον] τεύξει ἀσκήσας <b>elaborately,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 14.240; [χρυσὸν] βοὸς κέρασιν περίχευεν ἀσκήσας 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 3.437; [ἑανὸν] ἔξυσ᾽ ἀσκήσασα 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 14.179. \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> of personal adornment, <b>dress out, trick out,</b> ἀ. τινὰ κόσμῳ[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.1; ἐς κάλλος ἀσκεῖ \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<b>decks herself,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Electra” 1073; δέμας [prev. author] “Tr.” 1023:\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] —frequently in <i>passive</i>, σκιεροῖς ἠσκημένα γυίοις <b>furnished with</b>.., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Empedocles Poeta Philosophus 61.4; πέπλοισι Περσικοῖς ἠσκημένη 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Persae” 182; οὐ χλιδαῖς ἠσκημένον 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Electra” 452 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of buildings, παστὰς ἠσκημένη στύλοισι[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 2.169; Παρίῳ λίθῳ ἠσκημένα [prev. author] 3.57: _absolutely_, οἴκημα ἠσκημένον [prev. author] 2.130\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; σῶμα λόγοις ἠσκ. <b>tricked out</b> with words only, not real, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Electra” 1217:\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] —<i>middle</i>, σῶμ᾽ ὅπλοις ἠσκήσατο <b>adorned his own</b> person, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Helena” 1379, cf. Alcaeus161. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>], <b>honour</b> a divinity, <b>do</b> him <b>reverence,</b> δαίμον᾽ ἀσκήσω θεραπεύων[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “P.” 3.109; ἀσκεῖται Θέμις “O.” 8.22. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>practise, exercise, train,</b> especially in Prose and Comedy texts, properly of athletic exercise, <br /><Level3><b>__II.1</b></Level3> with <i>accusative</i> of person or thing, ἀ. τὸν υἱὸν τὸν ἐπιχώριον τρόπον[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Plutus” 47; ἀ. τὰ σώματα εἰς ἰσχύν 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 2.1.20, compare “Mem.” 1.2.19; ἐχθρὸν ἐφ᾽ ἡμᾶς αὐτοὺς τηλικοῦτον ἠσκήκαμεν 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 3.28\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]:—<i>passive</i>, σώματα εὖ ἠσκημένα[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 1.6.41; εἰς ἀγῶνα ἄμεινον ἡμῶν ἤσκηνται 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 9.52; ἀσκεῖσθαι λέγειν 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Demon.” 4; τὴν Κυνικὴν ἄσκησιν [prev. author] “Tox.” 27; λόγοις 2nd-3rd c.AD: Dio Cassius Historicus 45.2; ἐν παιδείᾳ [prev. author] 60.2; πρός τι 1st c.BC: Diodorus Siculus Historicus 2.54. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> with <i>accusative</i> of the thing practised, ἀ. τέχνην, πεντάεθλον, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.125, 9.33; λόγους 3rd c.AD: Democritus Epigrammaticus 53a, 110; μανθάνειν καὶ ἀ. τι 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Gorgias” 509e\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἀ. παγκράτιον, στάδιον, etc., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Lg.” 795b, “Thg.” 128e; ἠσκηκέναι μηδεμίαν ἄσκησιν κυριωτέραν τῆς πολεμικῆς 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Politica” 1271b5: _metaphorically_, ἀ. τὴν ἀληθείην, δικαιοσύνην, 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 7.209, 1.96; δίκαια 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Coloneus” 913; ἀρετήν 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Fragmenta” 853, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 407a; κακότητα 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 1066 (Lyric poetry), compare 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Trachiniae” 384; ἀσέβειαν 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Bacchae” 476; τὰ δίκαια 4th c.BC: Crates Thebanus Poeta Philosophus 12; λαλιάν 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Nubes” 931 (_anapaest meter_): with double _accusative_, ἀ. αὑτόν τε καὶ τοὺς σὺν αὑτῷ τὰ πολεμικά 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 8.6.10. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.3</b></Level3> with <i>infinitive</i>, ἄσκει τοιαύτη μένειν <b>practise, endeavour</b> to remain such, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Electra” 1024; λέγειν ἠσκηκότες [prev. author] “fragment” 963; εὐσεβεῖν ἠσκηκότα 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Fragmenta” 1067\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἀ. γαστρὸς κρείττους εἶναι, τοὺς φίλους ἀγαθὰ ποιεῖν, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 4.2.45, 5.5.12, compare “Mem.” 2.1.6\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἤσκει ἐξομιλεῖν παντοδαποῖς he <b>made a practice of</b> associating.., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Ages.” 11.4. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.4</b></Level3> <i>absolutely</i>, <b>practise, go into training,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 389c, 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 2.1.29; οἱ ἀσκέοντες \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<b>those who practise gymnastics,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “περὶ διαίτης ὀξέων” 9; περὶ τὰς βαναύσους τέχνας 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 9.20.9.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G0778","accentedUnicode":"ἀσκέω","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G4632","matchingForm":"σκεῦος","stepTransliteration":"skeuos","gloss":"vessel","_zh_tw_Gloss":"器皿","_es_Gloss":"vaso","_zh_Gloss":"器皿"}],"shortDef":"to strive, do one’s best","mediumDef":"to strive, do one’s best <br /><i>primarily</i> <b>to work</b> materials; <i>absolute</i> <b>to train</b> or <b>exert one's self, make endeavor, do one’s best</b> <ref='Act.24.16'>Acts 24:16</ref>*","stepGloss":"to strive","stepTransliteration":"askeō","count":1,"_es_Definition":"esforzase, procurar ; hacer lo mejor posible","_zh_tw_Definition":"操練, 努力 (徒 24:16)","_zh_Definition":"操练, 努力 (徒 24:16)","_step_Type":"verb","_vi_Definition":"cố gắng; gắng sức; trau dồi","_zh_tw_Gloss":"勉勵","_es_Gloss":"esforzarse","_zh_Gloss":"勉励"}]}